body:
## 🐛 Bug Report

When using Streaming xlsx writer, when any cell in the worksheet has a hyperlink in conjunction with any cell in the worksheet having a data validation makes the final excel file un-openable in Microsoft Excel with the following error message:

`We found a problem with some content in ’output.xlsx’. Do you want us to try to recover as much as we can?`

The file is properly getting opened in other applications like Libreoffice and WPS office.

Also, when using non-streaming approach (writing all buffer at once), it works fine with all applications.

Lib version: 4.4.0

Other env details:
MS-Excel version: Microsoft Excel for Mac (v16.86)
NodeJS version used: v16.15.0
NPM version used: v8.5.5

## Steps To Reproduce
The following code uses Streaming xlsx to write a hyperlink in cell A1 and a data validation (dropdown) in cell A2 and export it into an XLSX file:

```javascript
const ExcelJS = require('exceljs');

const workbook = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter({
  filename: "./tmp/output.xlsx",
  useStyles: true
});
const worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('Sheet 1');

worksheet.getRow(1).getCell(1).value = {
  text: 'http://example.com',
  hyperlink: 'http://example.com',
  tooltip: 'http://example.com'
}
worksheet.getRow(1).commit();

worksheet.getRow(2).getCell(1).dataValidation = {
  type: 'list',
  allowBlank: true,
  formulae: ['"One,Two"']
};
worksheet.getRow(2).commit();

worksheet.commit();
workbook.commit().then(() => {
  console.log('Workbook stream has been written successfully.');
}).catch(err => {
  console.error('Error writing workbook stream:', err);
});
```

## The expected behaviour:
The file should be openable in MS-Excel too when using Streaming xlsx writer with the above code
